<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870918-0171 </DOCNO><HL> American Air to Add Flight</HL><DD> 09/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AMRAIRLINES (AIR) </IN><DATELINE> FORT WORTH, Texas  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Airlines, a unit of AMR Corp., said it will begin a daily flight to San Juan, Puerto Rico, from its Raleigh-Durham, N.C., hub, starting Dec. 2.    The flight will connect with other Caribbean flights operated by American and American Eagle, its commuter airline partner, the company said. </TEXT></DOC>